  "prompt": "What are the best indie game developers?",
  "response": "There are many talented indie game developers known for creating unique and innovative games. Here\u2019s a list of some of the most acclaimed indie game developers as of my last knowledge update:\n\n1. **Supergiant Games** - Known for beautifully crafted games like *Bastion*, *Transistor*, *Pyre*, and *Hades*, Supergiant focuses on strong narratives and striking art styles.\n\n2. **Team Cherry** - This Australian studio gained fame with *Hollow Knight*, a stylish and expansive metroidvania that has been praised for its art, gameplay, and depth.\n\n3. **ConcernedApe** - The solo developer behind *Stardew Valley*, a beloved farming simulation game that captures the charm of classic games while being accessible and modern.\n\n4. **Devolver Digital** - Although a publisher rather than a developer, Devolver Digital has backed numerous iconic indie titles like *Hotline Miami*, *Enter the Gungeon*, and *Fall Guys*.\n\n5. **Thatgamecompany** - Creators of *Journey*, *Flower*, and *Sky: Children of the Light*, known for their focus on emotional experiences and unique gameplay.\n\n6. **Annapurna Interactive** - Similar to Devolver Digital, this publishing studio has released critically acclaimed games such as *What Remains of Edith Finch*, *Journey* (also published by them), and *Outer Wilds*.\n\n7. **Capybara Games** - Known for games like *Superbrothers: Sword & Sworcery EP* and *Below*, this studio is noted for its artistic approach and engaging gameplay.\n\n8. **Playdead** - This Danish studio is best known for *Limbo* and *Inside*, both of which are lauded for their atmospheric storytelling and striking visual design.\n\n9. **Nidalee** - Known for their unique art style and engaging gameplay experiences, particularly with titles like *Gris*.\n\n10. **Mobius Digital** - Developers of *Outer Wilds*, a unique exploration game celebrated for its innovative mechanics and storytelling.\n\n11. **Braid** (Jonathan Blow) - While Blow is often associated with the development of *Braid*, his further work on *The Witness* also solidifies his reputation in the indie space.\n\n12. **Tiny Build** - Known for a range of indie titles including *Hello Neighbor* and *Totally Accurate Battle Simulator*.\n\nThese developers and their projects have contributed significantly to the indie game landscape, offering players unique experiences that often contrast with AAA games. Keep an eye on emerging developers, as the indie scene continues to evolve and produce fresh talent.",
